column52: "">Parallels have been pointed out between the Ragnarök of Norse religion and the beliefs of other related Indo-European peoples. Subsequently, theories have been put forth that Ragnarök represents a later evolution of a Proto-Indo-European belief along with other cultures descending from the Proto-Indo-Europeans. These parallels include comparisons of a cosmic winter motif between the Norse Fimbulwinter, the Iranian Bundahishn and Yima.[53] Víðarr's stride has been compared to the Vedic god Vishnu in that both have a ""cosmic stride"" with a special shoe used to tear apart a beastly wolf.[53] Larger patterns have also been drawn between ""final battle"" events in Indo-European cultures, including the occurrence of a blind or semi-blind figure in ""final battle"" themes, and figures appearing suddenly with surprising skills."
